stories.text:
I am requesting suggestions for good quality paid news subscriptions that are easy to un-subscribe from.

I have heard that unsubscribing from NY Times and WSJ can be a pain because you have to call up a number to talk to someone about it, and evade any attempts they might make to lure you back in.

I am primarily interested in business/financial news. I looked at Bloomberg un-subscription process, and it seems they also require you to chat with the customer service about it.

Ideally I would like to subscribe (and unsubscribe) directly (i.e. not through, say, iTunes).

If you have any good experiences with unsubscribing at will, please share.
